frameDefinitions: A perceptible Figure shows up against a Ground location due to Light shining on/from it, its salience possibly dependent on a Cause_of_shine.
In this frame, the temperature of an Item changes.
An Entity (generally food) is exposed to a Heat_source whose Temperature may also be specified.
These words refer to Parts merging to form a Whole.
An Agent or Cause causes a Process or State to end.
This frame contains verbs that describe emotional experiences and participate in the locative alternation, as in the following examples: '' ' I was boiling with anger.'
frameExamples: The house had <t>cooled</t> <t>off</t> by a few more degrees by midnight, and we finally managed to eat a bite.
Bacon was <t>frying</t> in the pan, and a great heap of eggs already lay steaming on a plate.
The two droplets <t>merge</t>, and then travel down the windowpane even faster.
Bush may <t>lift</t> sanctions on his own, despite opposition.
listRoleDefinitions: The percept which is perceived at a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location.
The location of the phenomenon.
The <fen>Light</fen> which is emitted.  In this frame, it is usually incorporated in verbs and adjectives, and is the denotation of many of the nouns.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Figure</fen> is observed against the <fen>Ground</fen> location due to <fen>Light</fen> shining on it.
The spatial setting in which the <fen>Figure</fen> shows up against a <fen>Ground</fen> location.
The entity whose temperature changes.
The scalar property that the <fen>Item</fen> possesses.  This role is rarely expressed.
The time at which the change in temperature occurs.
The location at which the <fen>Item</fen> changes temperature.
The <fen>Entity</fen> (often a food item)  that absorbs heat.
The <fen>Container</fen> that holds the <fen>Entity</fen> that absorbs the heat.
This role identifies the object that directly supplies heat to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the heat absorption takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the heat application occurs.
The entities that merge to form a single <fen>Whole</fen>.
The single, undifferentiated entity that is the result of the amalgamation.
The prominent entity that combines with <fen>Part_2</fen> to form a <fen>Whole</fen>.
The less focussed-upon entity that the <fen>Part_1</fen> merges with.
The time at which the <fen>Parts</fen> become amalgamated into a <fen>Whole</fen>
The location at which the amalgamation occurs.
A <fen>Process</fen> which is ended by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The individual who causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to end.
An event that causes the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> to end.
A <fen>State</fen> which is ended by the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> is ended.
The location where the <fen>Process</fen> or <fen>State</fen> is caused to end.
The Experiencer is the individual that experiences the <fen>Emotion</fen>.

The Emotion experienced (usually restricted to words such as <ment>anger, fury, rage, passion</ment>) can occur as the External Argument or in a PP Complement. Alternatively, there may be no expression of Emotion separate from the target verb:
The words in this frame can occur with an overtly expressed Seat of the Emotion. This frame element occurs as a PP Complement:

Hot coals glowed <fex>behind the fire grate</fex>.
The fire <fex><t>glowed</t></fex>.
<fex>In the morning</fex> the grass glistened with dew
<fex>Outside</fex> something was shimmering on the shore.
The raw fish that is to be eaten as sushi has to be meticulously prepared and must first be chilled <fex>in temperature</fex> to exactly above freezing point.
<fex>Bacon</fex> frying in the pan and scenting the air
Five fat sausages were frying <fex>in the pan</fex>
Food was placed to sizzle <fex>on the barbecue </fex>.
<fex>Five minutes ago</fex>the eggs weren't boiling yet.
<fex>In the kitchen</fex> the meat sizzled in the oven and a big pan of potatoes stood on the hob
They had all just merged <fex>into one big file</fex>.
<fex>The single smaller soul</fex> merges with the Ur-soul.
The single smaller soul merges <fex>with the Ur-soul</fex>.
<fex>That move</fex> ended her political career, she said in a 1994 Times Union interview.
We should end <fex>poverty</fex>.
They ended their relationship <fex>in the same coffeehouse where it started</fex>.
<fex>Pat</fex> seethed with rage.
<fex>Rage</fex> boiled inside him.
Fury seethed <fex>within her</fex>.
